Python Interfaces
	pyPgSQL   
		for win32 (active as of 9/01).  Installs PySQL.py etc. into root of
		Python installation.  See source for doc.
	PoPy - DBI 2.0, best choice, (zope prod ZPoPyDA).  Rumor of win32 port
	psycopg
	ZmxODBC

Connection
	Python DBI 2.0
		o = psycopg.connect("dbname=template1 ...")
		o.set_isolation_level(0)
		c = o.cursor()
		c.execute("CREATE DATABASE xxx ...")


Zope
	Zope db connection string for remote dbs:
		database@hostname:port username

ODBC:
	FAQ on pgsl site
	Section in Developers' manual
	mailing list pgsql-odbc
	Pgsl and Access together: www.scw.org/pgaccess/faq.html
